      "amount": "1 teaspoon",
      "notes": "to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "black pepper",
      "amount": "1/2 teaspoon",
      "notes": "to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "fermented bean paste",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons",
      "notes": "optional"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a medium saucepan, sous-vide water bath at 190°F (88°C) for 4 hours to cook the soaked white navy beans.",
    "Drain and rinse the cooked white navy beans.",
    "In a blender or food processor, puree the cooked white navy beans, coconut oil, onion, garlic, ginger, fish sauce, and fermented bean paste until smooth.",
    "In a medium saucepan, heat the coconut cream over low heat.",
    "Stir in the pureed bean mixture and cook for 10 minutes.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Serve warm or at room temperature."
  ],
